		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Help to fellow casters about Specialization Skill</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:">Fellow Caster</a> | 
		            2/14/2000 11:33:43 AM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">	Greetings all Eq-addicts!  I have some information that I would like to share with my fellow casters about a topic that has personally frustrated me for a long time - Specialization.  <BR>
<BR>
	Here is what I have learned as of today, Sunday, 02/13/2000.<BR>
<BR>
	I waited 10 levels for my skill in Alteration, the skill that I chose to be my specialty, to hit the fabled 51 mark.  I spoke to several higher level necros during this time about it and they seemed to be telling me that it will go up on it's own in a few levels.  This was when I was 21-22.  I am now 32 and no increase. <BR>
<BR>
 So, I decided to try an experiment.<BR>
<BR>
	When I put my single point into Alteration skill (way back when I was 20), I neglected to put any more points into the other casting skills at the time (Thus leaving them inactive and unusable).  This was my big mistake, it appears.  Even eqcasters doesn't stress this little known fact about Specialization!  <BR>
<BR>
	And this is it.  The little known fact that kept me from being my best for 10+levels.<BR>
<BR>
	YOU MUST HAVE PLACED ONE PRACTICE POINT INTO EACH CASTING SKILL TO ALLOW YOUR CHOSEN SKILL TO RISE ABOVE 50!  <BR>
<BR>
	Sound simple, doesn't it? Some of you may be wondering why I didn't just place the necessary practice points into the other casting skills before I leveled today.  It is a simple explanation as to why.  I also was misinformed as to what to do with my practice points as I acquired them during my rise in seasons and I ended up spending them all on the wrong skills =(.  This is why I had to level.  I had to earn new practice points so I could actually try out what I had been suspecting for a while about the mechanics of  the skill  Specialization .<BR>
<BR>
Therefore, I am offering the following suggested guidelines, for all eq classes that  Specialize, to follow when this skill becomes available to them. Of course, the specific casting skill that you will choose will be dependent on your class and playing style.  Since I play a necromancer, and know it best, I will use the necromancer as my template example.<BR>
<BR>
1) First, place one practice point in the chosen field you wish to rise above 50.  You may only have one of your casting skills rise above 50, so choose carefully.  All the others will cap out at 50.<BR>
<BR>
2) Then, choose 2 spells that use that casting skill - for necros it is Alteration - and cast for a short while to bring your skill up to 50. You can do this on your pet to increase your skill.  I do not recommend combat as a good way to increase your skill because you may miss the message that it has reached 50 during one of your fights.<BR>
<BR>
3) After you have successfully raised your skill in Alteration, then you place one, and only one,  practice point into the remaining 4 casting skills (Abjuration, Conjuration, Divination, and Evocation) to &quot;activate&quot; them.<BR>
<BR>
4) Finally, you either cast Alteration spells until you see the message that you have hit 51 or <BR>
put one more practice point into it.  <BR>
<BR>
	And there you have it folks.  A potentially very frustrating experience like mine reduced to an easily understood set of steps so those eq players that have literal brains - like me - will not have to miss the point and not play at their greatest efficiency.   <BR>
<BR>
	Please include this information on your web site's news board so everyone may understand clearly how to make best use of this skill when it becomes available.  I will be glad to share what I know with any necros on my server if they ask me when I am on.  Thank you.<BR>
<BR>
	Vandaraa De'Vitch dark elf necromancer of the 32nd circle Quellious server.<BR>
<BR>
P.S.  I also make necro spells for free if the necro brings me their spell components and their dark bindings book.  I usually do not carry mine around when I am hunting.  If I have the word(s) they need I will only charge &#189; of the going rate for the words and no more.  We necros must stick together you know &amp;#61514;<BR>
