			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Specialization skill go up the same as other skills as in that when they hit 30 they go up easier, get easier again at level 40 too.  What I suggest is to put 10 points into your specialization skill (Alteration for my necromancer) and 1 in each of the rest...the skills you put only one skill point in will go up much slower than the main one you use...and will go up faster for two reasons.  1)  you are at skill level 30, so it will increase the rate that the skill increases.  2)  The one skill that is the highest should be the one that you use the most, so it should be going up fastest anyway.  By the time any of my other skills got out of the 20s, my alteration skills were in the 70s (for specialization that is.)  <BR>
<BR>
Hope this helps...it is a pain to train as the guy above said...it goes up fast in battle and you can feel free to burn some practice points here, what else are you going to use them for?  Your last skill is dodge at 22...and you should not be close enough to a MOB to worry with getting that skill til the next time you are in town, at 24.  I dinged 20, got my spells, a backpack 1/2 full of food, 1/2 full of drink, and se out...I am a bubble into 23 and still have not been to the town again...<BR>
<BR>
Taek, Dark Elf Necromancer<BR>
<BR>
Taek, Dark Elf Necromancer of 23 levels
